<p>The idea of Duet emerged when &#39;smart watch&#39; was climbing up the <a href="http://www.gartner.com/newsroom/id/3114217" target="_blank">hype curve</a>. Kind of tired of playing with the phone, I asked the simplest question: what can we do now that we have two mobile devices? I didn&#39;t start a project right away; in fact this&nbsp;idea didn&#39;t get picked up until a few months later when I interned at Autodesk Research. In retrospect, this project was the best experience I have ever had doing research, as I really took time to explore a wide range of things and the project evolved and incorporated cross-disciplinary aspects that, in my opinion, truly distinguished itself from most of my other projects, and most of the projecfs done in the HCI community.</p>

